  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "BIM Modeller",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Develop and maintain accurate 2D/3D BIM models using software such as Revit,  AutoCAD, or other BIM platforms.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with architects, engineers, and consultants to coordinate design information and resolve technical issues.</li>\n  <li>Produce shop drawings, construction drawings, and detailed documentation from BIM models.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all models and drawings comply with company standards, BIM execution plans, and industry codes.</li>\n  <li>Assist in clash detection, model coordination, and updating models based on design revisions or site changes.</li>\n  <li>Support project teams in extracting quantities, schedules, and other data from BIM models for project planning and execution.</li>\n  <li>Maintain proper documentation and ensure version control of models and drawings.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Architecture, Civil Engineering.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in BIM software such as Autodesk Revit, Navisworks, AutoCAD.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of construction processes, building systems, and design documentation.</li>\n  <li>Experience in model coordination and clash detection is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Good attention to detail, organizational skills, and the ability to work under tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication and teamwork skills.</li>\n</ul>",
